osed in the meeting between the professional practitioner and the client. The book uses many practical examples to help make the application of social pedagogy more accessible, and is ideal for students on courses covering work with children and young people. This translation has been carried out by Kirsti Spaven and is published with the financial support of NORLA.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aCritical pedagogy. 0aEducationxSocial aspects. 0aSocial work with children. 0aSocial work with teenagers. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Social Work.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995z9783111196213oZDB-23-BUPP0 cprintz978144730538540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447314301423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447314301/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-BUPPc1995d2013